<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-20T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="562" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–2051: Telegram</note>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the United States
                                    Delegation to the General Assembly</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Roosevelt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-20T19:00:00+01:00">December 20</date>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-21T19:00:00+01:00">[<hi rend="italic">21?</hi>], 1951—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 770. Re: <gloss target="#t_USGADel1">USGADel</gloss> decisions mtg 21 Dec.</p>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                            <p>2. Re Indians in South Africa item, joint draft res discussed. US
                                will vote in favor whole res if comes to vote before recess. On
                                para-by-para vote, US will abstain on third preambular para and
                                operative paras numbered 2 and 3. If vote postponed until after
                                recess, will communicate with <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                                re possibility stimulating introduction of res which will promote
                                and assist negotiations between parties.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>